Now, give me those ruby slippers or your dog goes into the river.
Those slippers will never come off as long as you're alive.
How about a little fire, Scarecrow?
I didn't mean to kill her.
It's just that he was on fire.
Please, sir. We've done what you've told us.
We've brought you the broom stick of the Wicked Witch of the West.
You don't need to be helped any longer.
You've always had the power to go back to Kansas.
And then I was back here.
Oh, but I wasn't all right, Aunt Em.
We kept asking people to send us home.
Anyway, it's all right because I'm home again.
And, oh, Auntie Em, there's no place like home!
I've heard Dorothy spin some yarns but that one takes the cake!
Wicked witches, talking scarecrows, lamb, what an imagination that child has!
They think I made it all up.
If there was only someway to make them believe.
Jerry, that's brilliant. They'll have to believe me now.
Uncle Henry, Auntie Em, will you seeâ¦  Yeehaw!
Reach for the sky you peyotes.
Where on earth did you get those things?
Ha ha! Our traveling Wild West Show got caught up in the twister.
It dropped spangled saddles and rhinestone boots all over the county.
Go back to work you clownsâ¦   They farm's still in shambles and you're playing dress up.  Looky there, even Dorothy got into the act.
We remember what really happened and where we were.

Twisters'll make a mountain out of a molehill.
Ooh! Well the good news is my Reverse Cyclonotron is still in one piece.
Now say we get, I don't know, another twister.
Oh, don't even joke about that, Hickory.
Well, this brilliant invention of mine will generate enough wind to blow that twister right back where it came from.
It's full of wind all right, just like it's inventor.
Well, the yard's not going to pick itself up.

You dare lay a finger on our animals, I willâ¦  Dorothy, please.
But Uncle Henry, they can't just come here and takeâ¦ I sympathize, neighbor Gale.
I was once a poor, dirt scratching farmer like yourself.
But as that paper from the sheriff clearly states, the law is on my side.
I won't stand for this, Lucius Bibb.
You can't just be taking our animals.
Oh, if you dare lay a finger on them!
Oh, now, now, Ms. Dorothyâ¦ It seems during the recent tornado, some of your uncle's pigs broke free and devoured my entire watermelon patch.
And as you know, I can't make Luscious Lucius' world famous watermelon barbeque sauce with empty melons, now can I?
Those aren't the only empty melons he's got to worry about.
Fortunately, I have a solution that will profit us all.
I'm running a big booth at the Kansas state fair.
I need meat, you need money.
So, I'm willing to take my payment in livestock.
Who gave you the right toâ¦  Now Dorothyâ¦  But Uncle Henry you can't let him takeâ¦ Why don't you run along and do your chores?
Why, there's gotta be a way out of this.
Oh yes, we'll give you all the eggs our hens lay for a month.
The only thing a chicken is good for is drumsticks.
You see? Mr. Tabby cat agrees.
Can't you give us just a little more time?
I'll tell you what, I'll give you 24 hours to scrape together the cash.
If not, I'll cart off everything that clucks, moos or oinks.
Well, I'm off to the fair.
Oh, you can keep the cat and mouse!
Well, there's nothing we can do but go into town and remortgage the farm.
Ah, we're drowning in debt as it is.
We'll all pitch in Mrs. Gale.
We can get odd jobs in town.
And I can hammer and paint and saw.
You could stay here, small fry.
Oh, but Uncle Henry, I wanna help too.
You can help by watching the farm.
That's a big enough job for you.
But this is my home too.
I want to help save it.
This is grown up business, Dorothy.
If you really wanna helpâ¦  Yes?
Boys, keep an eye on her.
That's all they think I can do.
Toto and I will take the house.
Tom, Jerry, you've got the barn.
May be we could fix those windows.
That'd show Auntie Em and Uncle Henry.
You're right. I've a funny feeling I should keep these close.
How do you steer this thing?
We better save the hello's until we get rid of him.
From Oz, the same as us.
Though getting back there might be tricky.
Until we do, let's have a look around.
So, this is the famous Kansas.
Not as bright and shiny as I expected.
Oh, I don't know. The locals look friendly enough.
Morning friend, how's the view up there?
Hmm, no need to act stuck up.
I must say, it's wonderful to see you again but, what are you doing here?
There's big trouble back in Oz.
It happened soon after you left.
On our very first Dorothy Day.
There we were in the town square.
Citizens of Oz, though our good friend, Dorothy Gale has returned to Kansas, we've built this statue in her honor.
And thanks to Glinda's magic potion, we can bring the statue to life for a whole day, oh, it will be just like the kid was here in person.
And remind us of all the good things she brought to Oz.
Things like peace, freedom, happiness and monkeys.
I don't understand, with the Wicked Witch gone, the monkeys have no reason to attack.
Oh, dear! I hereby banish you monkeys to the end ofâ¦ Ohâ¦ Cut it out!
Pick on someone your own size!
Put 'em up, put 'em up. I'll ride you airsick banana addicts.
Who's first? I'll take you all on!
Come back and fight, you big cowards.
And all this didn't compare to what happened next.
That is when I decided to take the bull by the horns.
I haven't any idea of what you're talking about.
Please fellas, tell me what happened.
Well, out came a horrible bunch of nomes, followed by the Nome King.
Oh, give me back my wand.
If anyone's gonna wave that wand, Glinda dear, it's going to be me.
Boys, I'd like to converse with the Strawman.
That's Mr. Ruggedo to you, brainiac.
And it's not about what I want, it's about what I get.
And there's only one more thing I want.
To destroy that upstart, Dorothy Gale.
I've never even met any Nome King.
You've made quite a reputation for yourself in Oz.
With the way you've been bumpin' off wicked witches, you're the one to beat.
After the Nome King threw us in the dungeon, Glinda used the last of her magic to help us escape.
Ruggedo was using his powers to make a tunnel to Kansas.
We followed his flying monkeys to warn you.
But that still doesn't explain why he would want to destroy me.
Glinda did say their magic is very powerful.
The Nome King scouring Oz for every magical doodad he can lay his grubby hands on.
It seems only his great fear of the Wizard kept him underground.
He would know how to defeat the Nome King.
But The Wizard flew away in his balloon.
Think, everyone. I'm sure the answer is staring us right in the face.
"Oz, the great and powerful "appearing for a limited engagement at the Kansas State Fair." Why, that's just down the road in Topeka.
If we can get The Wizard to return to Oz, I'm sure he'll set everything right.
I know. We'll go with you to show you the way.
Our friends would attract a lot of attention here in Kansas.
Uh, uh, does this make me look fat?
We'll take the old tractor, trailer and all.
I know they think I'm just a kid.
But I can do this. I know it.
Oh, won't you let me try?
You have to put fluid into a machine to make it run.
Well, this is Kansas, Tin Man.
Machines can't run themselves like they do in Oz.
WhooWhee! That stuff's got a kick to it.
Oh, Miss Tractor, would you drive us to the fair?
Ain't you a fine bit of craftsmanship.
I ain't had this much pep in my pistons for years.
Now, hands off the steering wheel, pussy cat. I'm drivin'.
Andâ¦ Stop pushing my pedals, mousey, 'cause it tickles.
Here we go again, off on another whirlwind adventure.
You got to watch them bumps.
I always wanted to be a hayride.
